            <path>Application.kt</path>
            file, you will see a call of the <code>greet()</code> function:
        </p>
        <code-block lang="kotlin"><![CDATA[
            fun Application.module() {
                routing {
                    get("/") {
                        call.respondText("Ktor: ${Greeting().greet()}")
                    }
                }
            }
        ]]></code-block>
        <p>
            This creates an instance of the <code>Greeting</code> type and invokes its <code>greet()</code> method.
            The <code>Greeting</code> class is defined in the <path>shared</path> module:
